HEADWORD: Uintatherium
<hw>U*in`ta*the"ri*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. <ets>Uinta</ets>, the Indian name of the region where the animals
were discovered + Gr. <grk>qhri`on</grk> beast.]</ety>
<fld>(Paleon.)</fld> <def>An extinct genus of large Eocene ungulates
allied to Dinoceras. This name is sometimes used for nearly all the
known species of the group. See <er>Dinoceras</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

